  <div id="readme" class="announce"><span class="name">README.rdoc</span><div class="wikistyle"><p>
To use these generator templates I recommend adding this function to your
bash profile.

</p>
<pre>
  function railsapp {
    template=$1
    appname=$2
    shift 2
    rails $appname -m http://github.com/ryanb/rails-templates/raw/master/$template.rb $@
  }
</pre>
<p>
You can then use this &quot;railsapp&quot; command instead of the
traditional &quot;rails&quot; one. Simply pass the template name as the
first argument:
</p>
<pre>
  railsapp base store

</pre>
<p>
That will generate a Rails app using the base.rb template found here.
</p>

</div></div>

    </div>
